X
(B^\top \otimes A) \operatorname{vec}(X) = \operatorname{vec}(AXB) = \operatorname{vec}(C)
AX = B \Rightarrow AXI = B \Rightarrow \operatorname{vec}(AXI) = \operatorname{vec}(B) \Rightarrow (I^{\top} \otimes A) \operatorname{vec}(X) = \operatorname{vec}(B)
\Rightarrow (I \otimes A) \operatorname{vec}(X) = \operatorname{vec}(B)
